The test suite consists of a set of test cases that are compliant with the OWL 2 Structural Specication (http://www.w3.org/TR/owl2-syntax/) and have a precise mean- ing under the OWL 2 Direct Semantics (http://www.w3.org/TR/owl2-direct- semantics/), but do not conform to the narrower specication of OWL 2 DL (see Chapter 3 of the OWL 2 Structural Specication).

The test cases represent certain family relationships and follow the style of the well-known "Families" ontology, which is used in the OWL 2 Primer for demonstrating the language features of OWL 2 (see Chapter 13 of the OWL 2 Primer, available at http://www.w3.org/TR/owl2-primer/).

PROGRAM SUMMARY Title of program: FormLink/FeynCalcFormLink Available from: http://www.feyncalc.org/formlink/ Programming language: Mathematica 7, 8 or 9; C;FORM4 Computer: Any computer running Mathematica andFORM.
We would like to note that FormCalc andFormGet.tm , mentioned at http://www.feynarts.de/formcalc , also use MathLink and pipes, but do not provide a general interface from Mathematica toFORM.
